<task id="013" project="smart-todo-decoupling-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Refactor LegalWorkspace legacy to-do references (CreateTodo + CreateWorkAssignment + useTodoItems) to sprk_todo</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: Shared-Lib Hoist (audit-surfaced follow-up)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4-6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>010, 011, 023, 030, 031</dependencies>
    <blocks>004, 005</blocks>
    <tags>react, typescript, frontend, fluent-ui, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Refactors a major consumer surface. Tags include `fluent-ui` + `frontend` + `refactoring`. Touches multiple `.tsx`/`.ts` files in LegalWorkspace. Blocks the final schema cut. FULL rigor.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>P2-W4</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches LegalWorkspace package extensively; other concurrent tasks (e.g., task 023 already done) modified the same package. Run alone to avoid conflicts.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Cleanup the remaining `sprk_event` / `sprk_todoflag` / `sprk_eventtodo` references in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` so the final schema cut (tasks 004 + 005) can run without breaking LegalWorkspace.

    Surfaced by waves 6 + 7 sub-agents (after tasks 020/023/031). Three sub-surfaces to address:

    1. **`src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateTodo/`** — LegalWorkspace's LOCAL CreateTodo component still writes `sprk_todoflag`. Replace with consumption of the shared lib's CreateTodoWizard (now sprk_todo per task 031). If the local component has LegalWorkspace-specific concerns (modal vs dialog, parent context, ActivityFeed integration), preserve those but route through the shared wizard.

    2. **`src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateWorkAssignment/`** — local CreateWorkAssignment with the same `addTodo` flag pattern that task 031 removed from the shared lib. Apply the same decision: remove the auto-create-todo feature; users who want a companion sprk_todo can launch the shared CreateTodoWizard with the work assignment event as regarding.

    3. **`src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useTodoItems.ts`** — still queries `sprk_event?$filter=...sprk_todoflag eq true` for the LegalWorkspace SmartToDo widget. Repoint to `sprk_todos?$filter=...` filtered appropriately (likely by workspace context — workspace ↔ regarding matter or project).

    Also clean up:
    - The R3-deferred TODO in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useTodoItems.ts` per task 023's note ("can only respond with a generic refetch — it cannot resolve a sprk_todoid to a specific row in its IEvent list").
    - Any straggler `sprk_eventtodo` reads in LegalWorkspace (audit Section 2C if applicable).
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke LegalWorkspace developer with shared-lib consumer expertise + Fluent v9.</role>

  <goal>Zero `sprk_todoflag`, `sprk_eventtodo`, `_sprk_regardingevent_value` (in todo path) references in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`. LegalWorkspace's SmartToDo widget queries `sprk_todo`. CreateTodo + CreateWorkAssignment consume the shared lib's new sprk_todo wizards. Build clean; cross-block sync via FeedTodoSyncContext (task 023 contract) works.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>The task 001 audit catalogued multiple LegalWorkspace consumers of the legacy event-todo model. Tasks 020 (SmartTodo) and 023 (FeedTodoSyncContext) addressed the SmartTodo + shared bus parts but explicitly deferred LegalWorkspace refactor. Task 031 fixed the shared lib's CreateTodo + CreateWorkAssignmentWizard but flagged that LegalWorkspace has LOCAL copies of these wizards that still write `sprk_todoflag`. Final schema cut (tasks 004 + 005) requires zero `src/` references to the legacy names — this task closes the gap.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateTodo/</file>
