  <notes>
    This is the final consumer-side cleanup before the schema cut. After this completes, repo-wide grep for `sprk_todoflag` should be clean enough for task 004 to remove the field from `sprk_event` without breaking any consumer.

    The LegalWorkspace ActivityFeed integration is the trickiest part — historically, events with `todoflag=true` were rendered as todo entries in the feed. Now todos are first-class sprk_todo records. The feed should likely show events AND todos as separate streams (or unified via the new bus, but with todo-id keying). Use task 023's FeedTodoSyncContext pattern.
  </notes>

